D’ailleurs, ChatGPT dit : 

Il est essentiel de faire une coupure à la fin de la saison, notamment pendant l’été, pour permettre au corps de se reposer et de se régénérer. Après des mois d'efforts physiques intenses, de compétitions ou d'entraînements réguliers, le corps accumule fatigue, microtraumatismes et stress. Sans période de récupération adéquate, ces petites blessures peuvent s'aggraver et conduire à des problèmes plus sérieux comme des tendinites, des fractures de stress ou des blessures chroniques.

Le repos permet aux muscles, articulations et tendons de récupérer en profondeur. Cela permet aussi de rééquilibrer les niveaux d'énergie et de préserver la motivation mentale. Une pause estivale aide à réduire le risque de surentraînement, qui peut entraîner une baisse des performances et un épuisement physique et mental.

En outre, la coupure permet de recharger les batteries, de retrouver de la fraîcheur et de repartir avec une meilleure condition pour la prochaine saison. C'est donc un moment indispensable pour optimiser la santé physique, mais aussi pour favoriser un meilleur équilibre entre performance et bien-être sur le long terme.

Activity Name: BYU Invitational 3K. Proud of everyone and my team.
Description: 1.86 to be exact with 8:04, missed the facility record by just a few seconds. This race was a lot of fun. I had more in me than I thought I did going into this. We had a few pacers trying to help us hit it, it ended up being off pace the first 800m, and I attempted to make up for it in the final 800m and couldn’t savage it, but that’s okay; we’ll get it next time. Christian is an absolute dog with how well rounded and versed he is in this sport. All of our SLCC team is knows how to work gruesomely. I truly come from an amazing team and am coached by the best man on the planet. Also can we talk about Aiden Troutner’s sub 4 minute mile? 3:59? At elevation? On the BYU indoor track? Shout out to Coach Wood and Eyestone for helping me get rid of my side cramp just seconds before the race on the start line before the gun went off. Shout out to Todd Garner for walking all the way out in the snow storm and back from his car to supply me with water because he wanted me to be as hydrated as possible for our race. Shout out to Riverton, Herriman, and American Fork XC|TF and parents for coming to watch and support me. And to all of you who came up to me today. Shout out to God. My sister and friends for coming. Time to do some more work so we can make even deeper history.

Activity Name: A much needed run with my friend, Justin Levine. ☺️
Description:
Justin Levine and I met at the Smith Fieldhouse today and went on a run. Now that I live in Provo, I have my friends I can run with regularly and I’m so grateful. If you don’t know, Justin was the one who paced me in the mile this past Saturday. We were talking about our friendship over the past few years on our run and he told me some really insightful things that inspired me a lot. I want to quote his words that he shared with me, just in case any of you could use some inspiration. 
 proud of yourself before accepting congratulations from anyone else”
 the nicest guy to yourself.”
3”Focus in on the thousands in your corner supporting you with positive energy, rather than dwelling on the few giving negative energy”
He has accomplished some amazing things in his career as a runner and hearing these words from him gave me a lot of gratitude to have a friend in my corner guiding me as I’m still learning to navigate this life with running. Feel free to give him a follow if you want and his instagram is: dreamers_are_undefeated ☺️ he’s a great friend to have around.

3 mile warmup. 2(then an extra one because I felt a little tight from racing Saturday.) then 16x400’s at 5k goal pace for this weekend’s race. Then cooldown/recovery missed mileage in the turf with my squad. The goal is to run 13:30’s or 13:20’s in this weekend’s 5k in Washington depending on how it goes. So coach wanted 65’s or lower. I hit mostly 65’s and a lot of 64’s and some 63’s. The goal of this workout was to teach me to pace myself and hit these splits without depending on a watch or another runner so that I can be prepared for anything. We all made coach really proud and it was fun to see his face right afterwards, the sprinters and mid’ d group went off as well. The unity was unmatched today and things are looking pretty good for us. God really showed up and carried us through. Beautiful weather today, thanks Mother Earth. 🌏 🙏🏾❤️. Tune in on TV this weekend.

Ran with Brigham to find Christian because I overslept from working this morning. Found Christian, got some miles in with him and Casey Clinger. Fun conversations. Grateful that my body is holding up fine from this past Saturday. Ran in Saucony Triumphs for recovery. Workout tomorrow with my squad.

What a race. I think I’m learning about Charlie Hardcastle’s “leave it all on the track” mantra. This race was tough. All I can remember in it was, “dang, what’s happening?” But I’m grateful. I got into a great race, a great heat and a great opportunity. Recap: Gun went off. I tried to get out with the two pacers. The heat was aggressive. Got boxed in and struggled to get out. Eventually got out and then decided to stay in 4th, relax, then sit and kick. The competition started to get heavier so I looked at coach for counsel. After about 2 more laps, I got in 2nd, then so many guys started exchanging leads so I decided to chill. Then I got passed by a few more guys and then afterwards coach told me the pace of the race was too slow so I decided to put my foot on the gas. When the pacers were done at 3k, I made a huge surge and took the lead. I held it for about 6 laps just hoping I’d have enough to conserve in the tank, and then I felt the heaviness set in. I kept the pace going and did a lot of the work. I ran tuff. The black out vision started to set in and I wanted to quit so bad, I still had 7 laps remaining. I dug deep and kept going. I got passed. Then made another surge, then got passed again, and again and again. Then I gave it my all in the final 800m, finished 6th and still secured the NJCAA record officially finally and PR’d by a mm of a second. I’m glad I finished the race when it got hard because we did what we came here to do. I knew my team was counting on me and I knew it wasn’t just about me. I prayed. Both coaches are proud. Family and friends are. And so am I. Thanks to everyone for tuning in on Flotrack. I did my absolute best to prepare for this race and I laid it all out there. I know I have a ton of work to do if I want to go pro by next year but I’m not giving up yet. And I’m grateful to have coaches that are gearing me in that direction. It was super fun also having Adam  Wood, his sweet sweet wife, and Rory Linkletter cheering me on. Time to enjoy Boston for the next 6 hours if I don’t crash on this couch from exhaustion after posting this. Anyways, God is great. #NYTJ #SLCCBelongs. PC: 📸 Andrew Lemay.
He’s gonna do something great today. So is Finn. Who’s checking us out on Flo Track today? My race is later tonight.
Shake out with crew w/concluding strides of 2x30 and 2x15 seconds. praying for a great day and miracle for us all tomorrow.

Activity Name: Camp Rock, Spiritual Giants, God, and Horses.
Description: This was a great run with God to just feel like myself again. After about 8 miles, I switched from my Hokas to my Sauconys and did the last 2 miles because I’ve been intentionally training in a heavier shoe just to get a little faster, and I wanted to see how my body responded to a lighter shoe to just kind of see where my body was at for this weekend.

Activity Name: Trying to Get back into my Rythm.
Description: 3 mile warmup, then (400/mile 1200/400)This was definitely not my morning or best workout. I was extremely tired, legs were tight from the plane, and I was just not in a good mental headspace. I already knew on the ride to practice that something was up. And I just couldn’t tap back into it. I started off really well but went a little too fast on the first 400m, (ran a 61 instead of 64.) then started getting better the first 800m of the mile. Then started going too fast again and then I tried to listen to coach but then I panicked because I wasn’t confident in pacing myself properly. (I’m new at this pacing stuff.)Then I started going too slow. Eventually got into the rhythm by the Grace of God and savaged a perfect split in the 1200m. Then was doing really well in the final 4 then my legs just got tight and I just knew it wasn’t my day. Everyone did amazing and I’m proud of my teammates for the fighters that they are, the work they put in and for the insane talent they have. Definitely had to go home and sleep, felt like absolute trash and it affected me mentally and I was pretty sad. Grateful for Coach Wood and Coach Aiden for reassuring me that I was still fine and that the effort is what mattered. warmup in Under Armor and Nike Vaporfly 3’s for the workout.  Didn’t cooldown. Been staying off Strava and just focusing on my mental and time with God.  That’s why I haven’t been uploading at all this week.

After the race, my workout was 3 mile tempo. With each mile being between 5flat and 5:20’s. I was tired and my heart beat was so fast so I didn’t hit the paces on the first mile, but picked it up and started going to average 5:07’s. Coach had me Treadmill at the university because it was cold.

Activity Name: 5k National Champ but crying because I will miss SLCC this Summer🥲 also this is prob my fav post race recap below ⬇️:)
Description: A weekend I won’t forget. 92 degrees and 98 percent humidity. Our team did great and I was able to pull it together for my team by the grace of God and win the 5k National Title with a lot of help and aid; I’ll get into that. First of all, shout out to Lindsie for being women’s 10k National champ and all of the All Americans that were born this weekend. Recap: the conditions were mind wrenching. It was blazing hot. This entire week here was, but man that 5k at 4:10 in the afternoon was something else. We were constantly having to apply ice cloths on our necks at all times up until the starting line, drench our heads, faces and shoulders with water, my body was constantly going in and out of it and it was a little harder trying to keep my body temperature regulated than I thought it would because it was tough. I remember Hunter, Jayden and I going into prayer after our warmup for God to sustain us minutes before the race. While we were on deck under the check in tent getting ready to go, we were all going back and forth constantly to get more water and ice rags as much as the race directors allowed us to before we were required to go out on the track for lineups and strides; however, we finally stepped out out on the track and everything changed. The gun went off and I felt a switch. Don’t get me wrong, the heat still was there, but it’s like I felt the host of Heaven out there grant us all God’s grace. Hunter and Jayden had this immense energy and they felt good, and I had this peace and I just knew this race was  going to be fun. The race started out and went out all over the place: fast, slow, moderate, tons of alternating leads, some aggression but also some bonding, all the opposite things going on at the same time;  I found myself on the inside of the rails, in the middle boxed in, off the rails, getting splashed with water cups, handing water cups to my teammates, (we were doing anything and everything we could to stay awake and be ON.) we had tons of fun and I even had some conversations with some of the guys from Trinidad, Pima, Iowa and New Mexico during the race and at this point it wasn’t only about winning, but to enjoy the process, celebrate each other for making it this far to the finals at Nationals in this HOT air and just let the race run itself and let whoever the winner be, be the winner. It became an honor and the stadium gained an enriching respect for us because they knew how tough this was being in this weather. The Spirit told me to turn my brain off, but to still be present enough to hear and listen to all of my coaches just in case race plans were to change, when to stay calm, and when to make moves. Around 9 laps in, I knew the race was mine. With 2k to go, I made my move,  but at this point the heat came back and I could feel the steam from my shoulders and my hair, and my heart grew humble as I knew I could still loose if I gave up, and I knew that I wasn’t a National Champion until I crossed that finish line. I looked around for my teammates Hunter and Jayden, and just trusted in God and decided to take it for them and the rest of my team. The temperature got higher but by the grace of God the pace got lower and I kicked faster. My team started going federal cheering NYTJ,NTYJ,  and let’s go JQ(x20) & my coach and friend Aiden raised my dad’s hat once again and I knew it was time to go, even if I was burning up, I knew that the Spirit of fire wasn’t unfamiliar and that gave me the courage to go.  I raised my heart to the Heavens and closed the last mile in 4:19 and saluted all glory to God at the finish. We did it, team. God is real and I once again say thank you. Proud to say, Nationals is now officially under wraps but my season still isn’t over. Your boy JQ is still in the game. The Olympic Trials is right around the corner and it’s time for me to get in GEAR as I’m racing the my special event that has my heart, the 1500m at Portland Track Festival. Excited for what’s to come and ready to work horrendously and pay my dues.  I’m grateful for Coach Wood for bringing me on this team, Coach Aiden for being one of my best friends ever, Coach Tom, Kelsey and Coach Tom for their endless support since we’ve been training in June. Also for Coach Tom’s wife and all the parents who came out and our athletic trainers who came out and made sure we were healthy, happy and equipped to compete this weekend. Shoutout to our friend, brother, teammate and camera man Nate for getting these amazing shots and photos of us as well. If you read it this far, comment a ❤️ :)

Activity Name: “I am the Head and not the Tail.”
Description: God is so good. This workout was cold and windy. 4 mile warmup, then coach wanted 6miles at 5flat, no rest in between just straight running) after saying a prayer on where I should do the workout the Spirit told me, “let’s go do this on the track.” (I normally do these types of workouts on the road, when I do them alone.) but with the Spirit guiding me, I felt in my heart I wanted to do this on the track for 2 reasons. (I knew I wouldn’t be stopping and I didn’t want traffic to interrupt me, and for reason 2, with racing the 1500 on the track in just a few weeks, I wanted to be more used to doing speed on the track as much as possible so that it wouldn’t feel any more foreign to me during the race than it should feel. with the cold and wind on the track, it started getting mental after about 2 miles in during the workout portion. I said a prayer to my Heavenly Father and Angels to get a prayer up and give me an extra set of legs. I wanted to stop but the Spirit told me to trust in God and in my coaches that if I did everything consistently in this workout like my coaches told me to do, then I’d be set to run at least a 3:37 at PTF in a few weeks if not faster. I stuck to it and remembered that I wasn’t just running for myself. But for God, family, friends, coaches, my team at SLCC, and for all of you. That helped carry me through, and to also remember why I wanted it. For this reason, this was my favourite workout I’ve ever done in my life. And I’m so much more mentally confident going forward in my running career after staying tuff in this workout. 6 mile cooldown afterwards. WU/CD in ASICS FF Blasts, WrkOut in Nike Vaporfly 3’s. ☺️🫡❤️

Woah! Literally so much fun. Followed and executed coach’s plan. Race went out hot, coach had me play it conservatively and sit at the back of the pack. Hobbs went out, and then the lead pack consisted of Jared Ward, Michael Ottessen, Me, Joey Nokes and Jake Heslington. The first few miles to me were all about having fun, staying relaxed and keeping these gaps closed as much as possible because these guys are all pro and elite so I knew I didn’t want to loose a chance at closing with any of them. About 1.2 to go, I knew I needed to start rolling because at this point I knew that finish line was going to be long as it always is at Des News, and Joey is super fast and Jake Heslington could close. I could feel him coming and my legs were starting to get tight. I feel like I was probably a little too conservative because I feel like I could have went a little faster and maintained and probably placed better, but I’m glad I listen to coach. As the last mile was a grind and I knew that I didn’t want to get out kicked, and get 4th, I prayed and secured 3rd. I’m very happy with how fast I can recover and get in shape. What a great workout this was as well. This is a good mental reminder for me that I’m feeling like I’m sitting in a good place for this upcoming and final cross season; however, I’m excited to work because I know Nationals will probably be a cat and mouse grind. God is great. (: 💗

Man. What. A. Race.!We all got out hard, the pack was aggressive, but fair. I’m really impressed, there were like 14 guys in the leading pack still halfway through the race. Then Casey Clinger put his foot on the gas, and then we went for it. After .5 miles later, it boiled down to Casey, Creed Thompson and me. This race felt pretty easy still for me(the high mileage is really helping me) but then I felt so good that I took the lead and made a surge .84 to go; unfortunately I wasn’t specific enough to know when to go and just went off of feel. I thought I had it, normally when I take a surge if I feel I’m going to win a specific race, I go for it. But I think I underestimated that Casey literally finished 5th in the Olympic Trials finals, and Creed also ran in the trials in the 10k, so these guys aren’t as easy to close on as other competitors that I’m used to running with. I kept the lead until 400m to go and they both passed me. I still closed pretty close to them and proud of what I did.  Even when I got passed, I still fought and didn’t let it get to me like I normally do if I get passed in races. I truly gave it everything in the tank the last 400 meters. Something I’ve learned in this race is that it’s a lot easier to succeed when you are running relaxed, calm, let the Holy Spirit guide you and when you feel like you belong in that group.  I’m excited to get to run with these guys again in Oregon in just a few weeks and see try it again with a much more conservative mindset. This was honestly super fun though. Also our SLCC team packed together like no body’s business and it was federal. I’ve learned a lot from today and it was probably the best race I’ve ever ran thus far in my career.   As the first race of the season, I’m feeling pretty great but I’m even more excited to work. Shoutout to Casey and Creed on 1st and second. :) #NYTJ

23:09. Keep working. The pack went out, rough start but maintained position well. We were moving. It was me, Casey Clinger, James Corrigan, Creed and Davin Thompson, Joey Nokes, Aiden Troutner, Lucas Bons and a guy from UCLA in the leading pack. At the first mile, there were a lot in the pack and it was super boxy. I was trying hard not to fall out of the tangents out of fear of getting DQ’d, but I tucked in and maintained. I felt great and around mile 4 I felt the lactic. I stayed and fought. First and foremost I’m grateful we got into Dellinger. The fact I got top 8 in this kind of race shows I’m working. Yet, I still have a lot of work to do. Our team did amazing. The conditions were perfect. I feel like I should have been further up at the end but I’m happy with a 23 flat. Less than a second from breaking 23. But hey, I’m still in the learning stages of this sport and I’m grateful we got to represent today. NYTJ. I’m not giving up and I’m still working. :) I am honestly really happy with this because it shows that progress is being made, but I’m going to keep pushing and do some amazing things. I have a lot more in the tank, and I’m eager to keep striving. It was truly an amazing feeling being in that pack in the final stages of this race and got to show that JUCO runners can run. And I’m proud of our team for beating a lot of D1 schools. It shows our coaches truly know what they are doing. Congrats on BYU today on their perfect score. 🤍

Have wanted to win this meet for a few years now, look back to grade 12 when I was the last guy into the fast section holding on for dear life. Now I’m winning the meet in 3:40.36, missing the time goal by 0.37 but overall a great end to the season ‼️
Nice solo 55’ progression run out here. 700ft elevation gain, never a flat part of the run, constantly up or down and a few huge hills in there (heart rate monitor on watch is dust)
+ 💩 break
Ran Marist yesterday, then did a workout after, got some rest and long ran today :)
Good run with the idiots

Activity Name: 4 mile tempo, 1 hill loop and 2 flat loops @T

Description:
113th, good thing it’s September 27th

Lots of work to do

Missed Ollie Boltz and Tristan Coles 
But great long run with Thomas Crockett
Honest work. Volume day 👍🏼
Almost 30 seconds quicker than Nuttycomb, 💩 race tho

Why doesn’t the music come out backwards and upside down Tristan Coles 

Thanks for the correction Tádhg Donnelly
Team W (34 straight), felt great, solid run heading into regionals.

Back to the treadmill gym setup this morning. More snow and negative temps today. Might get to double with some people on the indoor later on today. Miles on the tread in front of the heater like a lab rat

-11 degrees and snow this morning and for the weekend it looks like. Super thankful for homies hooking me up with a treadmill and looking out for me on days like this! Going to take advantage of the new spot a lot over next few weeks
Wanted one more run outside before the cold came. By my math, that’s 30 on the day. Let’s grub

Is Im going to get the work in. Absolutely miserable weather coming to boulder this weekend so went long today. Still battled crazy headwinds alone but took it for what it was. Quality work, double later
Sad to wake up and see Bill Belichick leaving the Pats. Wish he retired instead of going to a new team. 10 bomb with Kaylee then added on 3. Might sprinkle in a tread double later on

Got the infamous email from the landlord letting us know that rent is going up next year. Hate to see it. Countered it with a double with Kaylee and Kyle in the IPF. About 20 bones in there today, always grateful for it.
Taking that quote from heather with me forever now. Happy she recognizes the work being put in :) double later

Back at it this morning. 9 x mile on 800 float around 6:00 pace. Went 4:54, 4:54, 4:59, 4:58, 5:01, 5:01, 5:03, 5:02, 4:53. Mark wanted 5:00 pace for the miles, so felt good about that, even though let the float slip a couple times to get water and make sure I had my legs under me. Switched directions for 6-8. Lotsa lane 4 laps today
Cuppa miles warm up outside before IPF sesh to start the day
Last mile inside of warm up to get muscles warm
Been putting up some rookie calorie numbers recently and it’s been reminding me. I do miss the warm weather where I would take more time to eat lunch outside. Oh well

Woke up to a lot of snow that wasn’t supposed to be here. Oh well, first few miles had a case of stiff legs but moved through it. Suns out now and hopefully will melt things off for the double, but the national championship is later AND Kaylee is making KFC famous bowls later
Jog before settlin down to watch some football to cap off a big day of training
One of those workouts that has you looking forward to the nap as soon as the cooldown starts. Double later

5 x 2 mile with 1 mile float around 6:20. As much as I dislike float recovery, this one actually wasn’t that bad. Went 9:59, 10:07, 10:02, 10:16 (caught lackin), 9:49. For as much quality work I got in this week, this was great. Hopefully back to regular schedule now.
Location: Boulder Open Space and Mountain Parks, USA

Description: Can’t remember the last time I did 3 workouts in a week, but whatever mark says goes. Solo out there this morning but plenty of other people out
Location: Boulder Open Space and Mountain Parks, USA

Description: Jogged over to the Holmes house to pick up whoever wanted to run. Got talking about summer travel and turns out they are going to be in France around the same time I was looking to go! Might have to make it happen
When you can’t remember the last time you got chipotle, you’re in a critical danger zone. Double to try to get back into a similar training week routine

Last run with Kaylee before she heads out to Orlando. Got in 10 with her and then added on the last 3 tip toein over ice. Saw some of the homies out there today, always fun seeing people but not fun when they’re running faster than you
Watched the clouds come over the flatirons at work today and then watched the thermometer drop 20 degrees in about 90 minutes. Crazy! First double with Kaylee in a while
Opened the garage to let some cool air in but since I was soaked with sweat I started to get really cold really fast. Double later

Treadmill LT since the roads are still really sloppy out here. Mark wanted 10 miles at 53 mins but that felt a bit slow so I picked it up halfway or so. Closed in around 4:53, not sure if there’s a treadmill conversion or not, but there’s definitely a sweaty boy in the garage bonus here at play. Miss doing these long efforts in the summer
Warmin up on the tread for my first tread workout of my life, kinda stoked honestly. My Strava got a nice upgrade yesterday :)

Waited a bit for some of the ice to melt (didn’t) but wanted to jog around outside for the first time in a while. Hoping sun actually comes out or might have to run workout on tread tomorrow since there’s still a decent bit of ice out there
Looked forward to this one quite literally all day as I was goin hard in the paint all day at work. Would’ve been easy to skip this one but that’s not who I am! Time to relax

Woke up early to get run done before work meetings, but Kaylees car wouldn’t start so had to rely on the MINIVAN to save the day. Still got in 12 before dropping Kaylee off at her appointment. Crazy hectic day at work followed by a double later for the birthday boy.
Little tread double action before some dinner plans. Really hoping the sun at least melts the snow or else might have to migrate south
Dropped by some of the girls finishing up their run inside but then got the legs back under me. Nice to jog around the track and seeing people that I haven’t in a while. Double later

Even MORE snow this morning, could barely see driving in. Monday morning workout in the IPF! 10 x 1k with 2 min jog. Went 2:56, 2:57, 2:57, 2:57, 2:56, 2:57, 2:56, 2:55, 2:54, 2:48. Nice rhythm workout with a bit of a squeeze down. Mark wanted 3 flats then close, so went close enough.
Wore the tights inside to flex on mark and heather that I can tolerate the heat. Just for the warm up though. Fun to see koki before

Was going to sleep in and run later to catch the warm weather but there was a group meeting at 8, so went for it. Glad I did, hadn’t ran with anyone in a long while! Now gotta find something to do until football starts up
Earlier double before head to church but also was motivation to get to run at the warmest part of the day! So nice out, saw Katie but she had headphones in and was too cool to flip with me

1 mile warm up, 4 miles around 5:50, 4 miles around 5:30, 4 miles around 5:15, 2 mile cooldown. 2 neva loops and then it started to get a little muddy and slippery so stayed on the road. Haven’t done a progression workout like this before, lots of practice with patience. Double later
Location: Boulder Open Space and Mountain Parks, USA

Description: Got a bit of snow overnight but now enough to make the dirt too slippery. Of course the snow turned into mud and slush and I was wearing brand new white shoes but at least I don’t have to worry about getting them dirty anymore. Good day for a ~sauna~
Really surprised to see absolutely nobody out on the main part of bobo this morning. Didn’t really see many people until the end, which was peaceful for a while. Bouta crushhh a flat white
Always forget how much easier it is to go out for doubles when the days are longer and the weather is not freezing cold. Shorts and a long sleeve and not a doubt it would still be light at the end
Coolin down thinkin about work and how bad I wish Thursday night and Monday night football was still going. Going to have to crank into the modelo stash tonight. Double later.

Saw it was supposed to be low 40s and sunny but the sun came out for about a mile and then got cloudy and breezy and temp dropped again. 2 x 5 mile with 5 min jog. 5:03/5:06/5:12/5:10/5:06 then 5:03/5:04/5:15/5:11/5:01. Wanted to run the reps a little different from each other and did that well. Good session
Location: Boulder Open Space and Mountain Parks, USA

Description: Was stoked beyond belief to see Tayler  Tuttle finishing her run as I was about to start and get to talk to a homie in person! Seems like everyone’s either in florida or in school nowadays
Location: Boulder Open Space and Mountain Parks, USA

Description: Woke up early to get it done before optional 9 am meeting, but then realized there is the same meeting in the afternoon today. Got to take my time and let it warm up and melt a bit, and bobo was much nicer than yesterday. 9 x 20 second strides starting at like like 7 or so as well
Went Bobo to see how it’s progressing since most other dirt spots are drying up. Surprised at how dry it was actually! I miss running out there

Tried to switch up the normal route a bit today for giggles. Hopefully todays sun will melt snow on bobo enough to get on it tomorrow because I miss the dirt! 10 x light strides in there. Double later

Absolute sufferfest starting lil after halfway. Knew a lot of people would come back no matter what pace i was running, so really geared down. Definitely was hot, but it felt like more of a calorie issue, which I think comes from baking in the sun haha. Watched a lot of dudes drop out in front of me but I knew i was finishing that bitch! Finished it and saw a Lost Boys group in the stands about 800 to go and they were losing it. Still would line up again tomorrow for the fam. I’ll be back for this shit.
Is it a warm up if you’re already warm? Felt like more of a fit check
Partial lake loops checkin out the local mansions around here with Austin. He forgot to have us do the normal strides bogina mile so tossed that in at 4.5

Hoping today is a big announcement for me at work! Solo loop this morning, got caught up watchin too many car reviews for super cars last night… at least I know all the specs of the Audi R8 and Nissan GTR nismo now
Finally the day has come to get to the barber, haven’t gone in 2 months! Beauty of a morning jog. No coyote sightings today, but have seen 3 this week
Typical trailer park boys loop but couldn’t get it to 4.20 as I had to run a bit further so a dude didn’t back into my with his car hahaha
Caught in the middle of the local cowboys and farmers moving their cattle from one field to another. Got to stop and watch it all go down on a beautiful day
6 x 2 mins on, 3 mins off. Ons we’re around 4:45-4:50 or so, nice to stretch out and wind up the legs. Really nice morning for some quicker stuff. Light double later
Location: Boulder Open Space and Mountain Parks, USA

Description: Tights and 2 layers but the sun got HOT. Happy to take them off after a warm up
Location: Boulder Open Space and Mountain Parks, USA

Description: Really nice morning out there today. Nice mind cleanser before a busy day of running around with work and other stuff! 9 lighter strides in there for fun. Stoked on the chiefs game yesterday, cashed out all my bets yuhhhh
Got tricked into running a bit later with Ethan from Holmes. Thought I was giving him a nice little run but he was already 14 miles deep on the ropes. Earning my Super Bowl snacks today
Wanted to get a run in before the snow comes tonight. What if just once it actually didn’t snow when it was supposed to? Instead, the projected 3-6 inches will likely turn into a foot
Gotta stay in shape for my Rec basketball team, so went out for a jog. Nice morning out, body was sore beyond belief from Saturday and then the basketball game on Monday
Up late watching UFC and a few too many beers had me out for the count last night. Nice little jog sesh in the sun to open up the Sundayyyy
Still waiting to see my first cybertruck but I know there’s one in boulder now! Nice group run with Holmes boys for some snow day motivation
It must have rained before the snow came- the roads were an icy mess under the snow. Went on the dirt (mud) of bobo to make it better! Some exciting stuff solidified to be coming soon
Nice to get back in double digits on the classic lollipop loop with Charlie. Cold and foggy moody morning. Hopefully some cook stuff coming in the pipeline today in the life of chuck

Always down to rip some easy miles from tom watson with homies. Nice to get on dirt and away from the usual out and back this morn. Talks about tryna figure out the whole running circuit system and eliud’s shooters in Kenya

Forgot how sore basketball gets you. 2 games deep and been a walking corpse after both of them, but so much fun. Those guys go hard in the paint at all times. Waited for weather to warm up a bit today
Basketball game later tonight, went out for a run to get the legs ready for it. Stoked on the chiefs winning last night, now my team has to come t through and catch one too

Joined in on the team run today for some company and to get out to big tex. Wanted 15 but a group was goin 16 so I bit the bullet. Not as wrecked as I thought I would be, but we’ll see how the legs feel later, especially in the basketball game tomorrow
Figure 8 loops with Aaron T2 on a beauty of a morning. Also going to come back to Harper lake to try and catch some of the largemouth/rainbow trout they have stocked in there someday

Chilly morning and then the wind started, and of course the wind switched directions as well. Was going to do a normal route but cows were on bobo just standing and staring at me. I lost the stare down and had to flip around

Today is National margarita day! Hopefully will snag one after a long day of work. So stoked F1 is back to testing to replace the void that football has left in my heart now. Cuppa cold days and then a warm weekend on tap
Austin texted me last night asking if I wanted to catch a run! Can never say no to a homie wanting to run so for some in with him. Dropped him off at 8 and looped around for longest run in a while!

Wanted to go a bit earlier so I wouldn’t be rushing to work, but when I woke up it was insanely windy out. Gave it some time and it really calmed down so went for what I could get in! Bloody toenails are back
Livin the life of a pro runner this morning with no work today. Got to wait until it really warmed up to go out runnin on the dirt. Drink beers with the BOYS

Huge crew on a super windy morning to get a good longer run in. It never snowed but the whitecaps on the boulder res were nuts to see. Couple different add-ons as the group had different distances but really enjoyed the time with homies. Sad I missed Benjamin Fleming post run selfie

6 miles to start it with Jenny, Jason, and Kaylee and then I added on around the Marshall mesa singletrack loop. I think this must be the first weekend the trails were open because it was packed! Always nice to touch some trails now and then
Beauty of a day outside with a bit of a breeze in one direction. First 6 with Kaylee to start and then added 6 back on bobo. Really nice weather, might have to get some hoopin in after work later

Queue the millions of emails with subject line LEAP DAY DEALS! Already at 3 for the day. 10 piece with some of the roots group, if you want random conversations that will always circle back to talent vs. hard work, join in on one of their runs

It’s back! Got one episode in last night and hopefully another one at some point today. I love that series so much and can’t wait for YUKI’s episode. First 5 solo, next 5 with Kaylee, and added on 2 more for fun

Should’ve known something was coming when the temp dropped 5 degrees since I woke up and the dark clouds were rolling in. Knew I was in trouble when the cows were taking shelter. Then the hail started followed by snow, followed by rain and wind! Just me and my shorts out there tryna get home. Boulder spring is wild
More wind this morning so tried to go north-south as much as I could. Got caught in a little sun shower for about 3 minutes which was crazy! Ran into Kaylee with about 3/4 to go and outkicked her

Stayed up pretty late watching the UFC card last night and woke up this morning to find out it was daylight savings (of course). Really wasn’t sure how this would go but duked out 20 with the boys! Felt better than I thought 5 hours of sleep would, time to go back to sleep
Nice to sleep in this morning and let the temperature warm up at the same time. Saw Jenny and Jason around mile 3 and then dropped off Kaylee at 7. Might try my hand at an 18-20 piece tomorrow

Started out solo before going back into work today, then ran into CU guys running Z2 double. Joined them for a bit then looped around and picked up Kaylee. Saw some homies running the opposite direction as well. Surprising how many people are out in the snowstorm

First day of in person work simulation on deck today, followed by a super cool COROS athlete dinner tonight. Excited for today and excited for things to mellow out at work tomorrow. Moody foggy boulder morning today
First double in a long while. Took out the PACE 3 for fun, and a lady told me I have beautiful form. What I’m hearing is wear the PACE 3 and get beautiful form?!

Even more sore today than yesterday from basketball. Assuming working a huge day yesterday also contributed to it, and now we got snow coming tomorrow. Going to hope to get out for a double later before the cold weather rolls in

Went hard in the paint last night at basketball so wasn’t expecting much more than 8 miles today. Loosened up and felt better than I thought, so went about 6.5 then picked up Kaylee for 5. Also forgot to say but this past weekend I saw a Nissan GTR, Porsche 911, and Audi R8 all in boulder. Absolutely INSANE
Out running around buff ranch and got to take a break and let a Great Dane for a little while, incredible. First day of low wind in a minute was really nice. Basketball game later !

Joined the team for long one for some company. Wasn’t sure how far I wanted to go so went 16 and chatted with koki for a while of it. Then went and looped around to make it 18. Might have some cold weather comin back this week, hoping it says Sike right now

Didn’t even try to get a spot in tom Watson, it was packed to the brim! People started parking on the street it was so crowded. Very nice 10 piece with Kaylee and Mackenzie and added on around the lake looking at the fish
Knew Jenny would be doubling today so texted her if she needed some company. Nice ti be in the other end of the extreme hunger on a double, she was starvin!

Trying to map out a good training/racing schedule in the ole noggin. Turns out having an agent is a lot more important than I thought it would be in this running stuff. Oh well, what can ya do! First 7 with Kaylee then added on 6 with a Tai Dinger flyby at the last mile

First run of the year where I noticed it was getting warm and dehydrating out! Wanted to see what the Marshall loop was since I forgot and it’s 6.9 (nice). Also had to bring out the gem of Mr. Steratore in honor of the MADNESS TODAY

Absolutely empty bobo this morning which is surprising because the snow is all gone. Soon enough it’ll be shorts and just a long sleeve weather, but I think there’s one more cold front coming… everyone welcome Jakob to the COROS fam

Wanted to get out and enjoy the sunshine after work. Absolutely missed doubling after work instead of during, sooo nice. Got super hungry halfway and fantasized about gummy peach rings for the rest of the way. Also a Stacey from work flyby!

Lots of familiar faces our around manhattan and bobo this morning, but time crunch didn’t allow for any shared miles. First 6 quicker to build myself a time cushion to run with Kaylee for the second half of it. Probably going to get out and jog a bit later

Saw a homeless guy putting on deodorant at the bus stop, so chill. First 7 with Kaylee and then thought I had a 6 mile add on loop but it was only 4, which made it drag on the last bit. Finally going to get the truck today :)

First shakeout after a long run in a long while, decided it was too nice to sit and watch March madness any longer so tossed in some music and went! Wanted to jog slow but gasolina turned on and it was over

Tagged along with the CU guys for a bit today. Got to around mile 12 and felt good and wanted to speed up, and convinced Koki to come along. Got some good miles in then stopped and saw heather driving away with all of our stuff inside. What a bummer! Oh well, easter Sunday good vibes with a big training week ahead

Been my favorite running spot in boulder since the start and I still think it is. Tagged along with Kaylee and Mackenzie before the buffs game today. Saw boulder favorite Marquis Bowden wrapping up his sesh with his homies after too, good vibes
Don’t get to run in the rain too often in Colorado, so tossed on my new jacket and got some fun in with Kaylee! Really been craving a milkshake, hoping sweet cow got my flavors in this week

Just barely beat the rain! Looked gloomy all run but never rained. Some morning miles with Austen and Mike. Hoping this is only rain and doesn’t turn into more snow again. Hoping to get in a golden hour jog later

Really nice weather this morning, surprised how empty bobo was. 7 with Kaylee and added on, tan around manhattan track since they’re on spring break. I can’t remember the last time I was on a track, fun to jog on it again. Might see if I have time to go for another jog later

Latest run start of the year and still bright out! As we get closer to Boston, wearing the shirt that Jamie Markham got me from Boston last year has people asking me if I’m running it. Oh well, not this year

Met up with some of the Holmes boys and Kaylee before they head off to Stanford this weekend. Remembering last years antics and memories had me nostalgic, wish a pacer was needed there or at Azusa. Still on call if anyone wants one!

Got the late text that a basketball team was short some players last night so popped out for a game. Ended up recording a career high in points but was super sore this morning. Cold weather made it hard to get out the door, but Kaylee and Koki made it easier for miles to go by. Maybe a double later

Thunderstorm last night turned into a crazy blizzard and left 4 inches of snow overnight. Didn’t really wanna go out but found time between some meetings and jogged around with Kaylee. Might have a basketball game tonight!

Solo out at Davidson, wanted to go at least 15. Got 3 laps in, grabbed some water and tossed in the AirPods to keep myself company. Really nice weather, always a breeze and the sun was so warm. Saw Kaylee and the little doggies around 15! Weather makes me excited to start cranking miles soon

Wanted to simulate the late night in n out so opted for some chick fil a at 8:30 pm last night, wild boy hours! Beauty of a run, definitely got to work on the tan today! Tryna find something to tag along with for tomorrows run
First shirtless run of the year yuhhhhhh! Finally they came, can’t tell me you’ve seen many nicer looking color ways! They comfy too, likin them so far. Hopefully they can handle the miles

A bit later of a start after taking care of some cats I’m pet sitting. REALLY nice day out, first 7 with Kaylee then decided to toss in the AirPods and enjoy the sunshine. Going to get out later for something slight in my new shoes !

Third sendoff run in as many days! Happy to have people who wanna spend their last run in boulder with me, but definitely missing out on traveling for races in the spring. Nice morn with Austen, REALLY hoping my new shoes come today
6 miles prior to company showing up, then touring around Lobo for the Erin Jaskot send off followed by coffee and vibes with boulder legend Marquis Bowden

Woke up to some sad news about some track logistics from my high school. Sad that things are able to be taken from the best coaches around just because people don’t agree with them. But got better with some miles with Kaylee, Austin, Paul, Caleb, and Noah. Kaylee even went 9… had people for 9 miles today yuhhhh

It’s nice to not be running as much so I actually feel human on my doubles and not just a moving corpse. Got moving on this one because the wind was coming from the east and wanted to try and see if I could make each one faster. Passed about 6 high schoolers like they were going BACKWARDS

Still no wifi but have data, might try to pull off the hotspot for todays work sesh. Got to do the good ole 6 mile double loop back to the house to pick up Kaylee and then add on 7 more… super nice outside and saw some homies along the way, thinkin a jog later if it’s still nice out
Nice weather double to top off the week. Who woulda thought speed workouts wouldn’t amount to as much mileage as a double aerobic sesh last week

Smaller group today but avoided lots of mud. Went around some loops I haven’t been in before, and Tai went 18.5 so had people for majority of it! Had to post this video, thought of it in the middle of the run and made me laugh out loud! Suns finally out again
Absolute pouring and snowing when I left the house but couldn’t bail on a blue collar run. Actually got much better and wasn’t bad for the most of it. Now tryna find a spot to take the truck muddin

Got out jogging and saw lightning but ran towards the sun. Super nice for a bit but then got caught in some rain so dropped the phone off at the crib. Don’t mind running in the rain so went out more, but started seeing super close lightning so called it at 6
Tried to convince Elise to go 5 for the cooldown but couldn’t. Had Johnny and doggie for almost all of cooldown. Big ol double later

SPEED SESH but also throw in threshold miles to make me happy. Not sure how many road guys are rippin 57s and 43/28 for fun. Really wondering what I could go for 5k right now. Over under has to be at 13:42 I would think. Might have to put my money where my mouth is soon
2 x in a row that i almost hit every single light in the way to Niwot. Just a few late though, all good

Yes sir Mr. Runner guy on Bobo, whatta day is right. Big release day for COROS, beauty of a weather morning, and wake up call at 3:15 am this morning. Felt so much better today than yesterday thanks to the Costco cookie I ate at 10 pm

Bad quality night of sleep made this one a struggle to get out the door. Still got to watch an Avalanche W, but went downhill after that. Oh well, got a good run in and even some shirtless running in there to add to the fun!
Running a bit mileage week last week and but also running.m a few speed workouts got my legs ready to disintegrate. Taking reservations for chipotle on Friday
Tryna figure out why Elise says the wolf of Wall Street is “too intense”… any ideas? Totally lost on this one

Insane workout on a Tuesday morning, started with a 57.7 and then had a full workout afterwards to top it off. So crazy to be running in spikes again after a marathon build fall, but this shit makes me so happy to be able to do still! Possibly one of the highest quality work days in a long while
Nice warm up in the sun and caught Ben for it too. Haven’t seen him in a while and was nice to see him out runnin again!

Really nice morning with a breeze to open up the week. Still a little sad that another weekend was messed up with snow, I just wanna play MINI GOLF mannn. Interesting pacing developments last night, might find myself in Cali if the cards play in my favor

Shoutout Lauren Keller for hookin me up with a couple pairs of Adi shoes. Gotta find out how to fit in the Bostons into the rotation now, and also ready to take on the trails with my first pair of trail shoes

Had no idea there was such as loop as this, thankful for Tai showing me! Ran into some rogue cows on mile 15 and had to wait for the farmer to come and get em. So incredibly stoked to be able to sit in the truck bed after runs right now and vibe rather than stand around

Really nice morning , glad I stayed in and watched F1 to let it warm up. In the last 5 miles there was a lady with 2 kids in a stroller just MOBBIN on the same 400 meters of bobo back and forth. Also stopped and saw the stocked the river with rainbow trout and hungout with those guys for a bit
Val and Kyle be runnin SLOW these days! Was thinking of going longer but got real hungry and it got hella cold so just called it good
Saw the biggest wild snake I’ve ever seen but only because tai pointed out that I ran right by it. Longer jog to make up for possibly not double workout

Tai Dinger is that guy! Wanted to help him with a barn burner of a sesh so hopped in. Started with 900 meters coming through at 2:05, then some threshold 800s, then helped take him through 400 of his 3 x 600 at 63-64. 4 200s at 27-28 and then more threshold stuff. Video is actual footage of us at the track today. Go nuggs
Tai and I tasked with holding down the Niwot fort today for the workout. Well really tai is but I’ll help

When you volunteer to pace a OTQ 10k out of the goodness of your heart but the compensation gets reduced to a point where you would be net negative money on the trip. Just tryna help some homies out man, throw me a BONE

Called it from the start- 4 miles 30 mins. Got to 2 miles at 15:05 without even checking splits. Negative split to get back with some time to spare… hope the insta reel goes as hard as I think it does
Rapidly approaching a deadline that I have to make a video for, bouta go see what I can solo shoot. Really nice morning, wish the workout yesterday was today haha. Possibly a little jog later
Beautiful dusk cooldown on lobo with tai, really felt like summer for a bit and tasted like it with all the bugs
Crazy headwind that didn’t translate to a tailwind combined with the sun behind a singular cloud made the quality work tough for all today. But still got some good turnover and threshold stuff in.
Funniest and craziest warm hours I have had in a long long time. Makes waiting this long throughout the day worth it off the rip
Moved workout to later on tonight to avoid the spring storm comin in. Saw koki and Jenny and caught some miles while chatting with them which was great. Then the first rainbow of summer came out!

I knew some of bobo was flooded after my double yesterday so wanted to check how high the little river next to bobo was. It was stupid high and flowing with white water! 6.5 solo, then picked up Kaylee for another 7 on the same route because I had to show her how crazy it was
Memorial Day sunglasses sales goin crazy, but there are so many different styles on this world it’s nuts. Just want some cool guy shades

Shirtless from the start to try and get tan but it was hella windy and I regretted it. Oh well, farthest I’ve gone on mags and had tai for 18. Missed running up here and the dirt high country roads! Many bolder boulder people “pre-meeting” at Mags today, crazy move. But nice people to chat with

Errybody out mowing and gardening this morning gettin ready for summer. Consuming a muscle milk and a whole bag of lifesaver gummies last night had me feeling right this morning! Ready to nap and watch pre classy later
Second double sesh of the week. So happy to be back on Manhattan too- 6 x 1200 with 45 sec rest. 3:46, 3:40, 3:43, 3:37, 3:37, 3:29. Little breezy but nice to work with Tai and get volume in
Short cooldown for 20 on the day lessgoooo
Short warm up but making is as long as possible to get the ole legs awake again.

4 x 1.5 miles with 90 sec rest around Celeeeeeezzzyyyy with Tai. Had the mile splits on my watch, tai had full splits so ask him for those. All should be under 5 min pace. Missed those types of workouts, been on the track too much recently! Included cooldown on the activity for the vibes
Checking out the celestial loop and the warm up spots associated with it, tai only took one wrong turn so he must not be a local

Really nice loop for this type of stuff but wanted to make sure effort was right after travel and what not. 15:25, 15:23, 15:18, 15:01. Really enjoyed progressing down on a cooler day, but got a little spicy at the end. Going to be thrashed after double and weights later
Slept in a little since the temps are cooling off but still started with a damn near empty Watson parking lot. Not quite blue collar but not white either

As soon as I opened the door and checked the TV the national anthem was playing before the FIRST NFL GAME OF THE YEAR, perfect timing for a run. Always be forgetting how LIGHT the PACE 3 is, surprising every time

Busy busy day at work but capped it off recording a podcast which was so fun! Double with koki at Davidson to force myself to go to Costco after… bouta rip a hot boy Costco dinner

Tried out a new loop and ran into the roots guys and Wilson and Mike. Told Noah I thought this loop would be around 12, and it would’ve been perfectly 12! Added a small loop of 8 strides at the end to polish 13 piece off. Double later
Hate to find out you had a tailwind the whole first half when you flip into a chilly headwind. Had to loop it around construction on way back which made it even more hilly sheeeeesh.
Actually able to run the cooldown which is progress over last year stumbling around not able to move, must be a bit stronger than I was

Wayyyy tougher than I gave this one credit for going in! Let the pack go at mile 1 and never really had the wheels to close the gap on many. Much hillier than I thought it would be but runnin high 4:50 and low 5:xx felt smooth, just cumulative fatigue in the legs I thought I could run from haha. Closed well over last 2-3 and caught 4 people I think? Trusting I’m in a strength shape and not as much speed to run a flatter course in a few weeks for a bigger focus. never a soft day on USA roads
Back in the road warm up routine vibe, missed it! Sweaty boy already

Baby boy long this week but got to link up with koki for 12.5 of it which feels like forever since we last ran. Not really anyone out running, but we got caught in a bike race about 11 miles deep hahaha. So glad I stayed up to watch UFC last night too, was so good

About to crush some Trader Joe’s pumpkin spice pancakes like never before

Very empty morning at Niwot even with a late start… where is everyone at?

No coffee this morn but just a little 9 mile guy so was able to trudge on! Shorts and long sleeve weather on these mornings is so niceeee. First 7 with Elise and then jogged around until I was ready to do 10 standing strides

12 mile lollipop from the crib but little did I know I would see a coyote, straw dogs, 3 bobcats, and a wild turkey sheeeesh. Bobcats actually scared me since I’ve never seen those things before, they were mad cute though

Double from Kyle and Val’s house while Kyle was at work but Val wanted to go on a bike ride so worked out well! Happy she wants to chat with me about contracts and what not, means a lot coming from an Olympian
Expedited cooldown to get back in time for a meeting at work but only had time to take it from Tom Watson. Most popular running spot -> home office

Madddd traffic on diagonal highway that had cars going slower than me running! 4 mile, 2 x 2 mile. Went 20:06, 9:58, 9:50. Was told to not go rogue and press any type of effort so kept it controlled and within reason. The long sleeve almost stayed in the whole time too
The one line Simon said to me while we were both awake at 6 am this morning at the house and it was 40 degrees outside

Planned out my early run AND strides with people to end up right before my meeting. Then logged on to the meeting but my entire work platform froze and crashed and I was locked out having to log back in for 10 minutes frantically trying to log myself back in sheesh. Great run and strides but miserable meeting execution… 2 miles sooo, 10 with guys, and 10 standing strides after

Holyyyyyy! What a dayyyy out there. For whatever reason the pacer for 64:30 through halfway wanted to run 63:30? Reed, Colin, and I kinda dialed it back and came through half around 64:30. Knew that was ambitious but was cruising and flowing well. Reed left me at around 17 and I started focusing on getting as much cals in as possible. Started feeling some cramps at mile 24 and got mad scared but fought them off enough to hype up the crowd for the last mile or so. Sounds like 20th overall and 8th American? Not as fast as I truly think I can go but 80 second PB will do just fine :)
5th on the segment let’s gooooo

Had a mapped out loop downloaded to the watch but it was closed off so I just followed runners and it led me to the lakefront! Really pretty run and lots of people out to people watch. 8 standing strides at the end, and can we talk about how I didn’t get lost let’s gooooo
Fitness center charges for treadmill access but homie told me I can slide for the 15 mins I needed it for. Clutchhhhh
Morning wake up call and run with Charlie and Austen, make that 3 talent loops on 3 days sheesh! Let’s make some magic happen

Opted to hit dirt roads today rather than lobo. Missed all the homies runnin earlier but wanted to get some good sleep. Still saw Daniel rollin out of Watson and imaginary ran with Austen Dalquist on his fav Boulda loop. Possible Bailey Kowalczyk sighting off of the trails?!?!
Still shirtless runnin in October? We take thoseeeee! Time to get some food in me

The usual rippin around IBM loop! Mile, 2 x 800, mile, 2 x 1 min. Tossed on some new shoes too and those boys are fastttt. Went 4:37, 2:26, 2:26, 4:44 and then the minutes. Lil faster than I expected or needed to go, but vibes are vibes
Warm up on the canal with Elise then saw Charlie and Spencer in the parking lot and got caught chatting it up with them for a bit so kinda accidentally cooled down haha
Absolutely in love with runnin lobo when the leaves are turning and falling off the trees. It’s so calming and makes it go by quick as hell! 10 standing strides back at Watson afterwards
